         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Stategarden 14/3/67. ¶  ¶ Yesterday, dear Mr Ramsay, I received the fine series of ferns from the New Hebrides, collected by my old travelling companion Richards. ¶  I will gladly name them, but as it...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.03.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562 Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-9, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS envelope front: '<seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">On her Maj. Service</hi>
                     </seg> | Edward P. Ramsay Esq. | Dobroyde | near | <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Sydney</hi>
                     </seg> | Ferd Mueller, FRS.' Front stamped Chief Secretary's Office, Victoria, and Melbourne, 14 March 1867.</p>
               </note>Stategarden 14/3/67.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yesterday, dear Mr Ramsay, I received the fine series of ferns from the New Hebrides, collected by my old travelling companion Richards.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H. Richards, who was a stockman on the North Australian Exploring Expedition, 1855-6? An 'H. Richards' is reported (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney mail</seg>, 14 June 1873, p. 745) as having been a botanical collector in the South Sea Islands.</p>
               </note> I will gladly name them, but as it will in some instances require critical comparison, you must kindly allow a little time, for at this moment I am preparing a portion of the material for the fourth volume of the plants of Australia,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Bentham (1863-78), vol. 4, published in 1868.</p>
               </note> &amp; the intercolonial Exhibition duties<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Intercolonial Exhibition of Australasia, Melbourne, 1866-7.</p>
               </note> have brought much other work in arrear.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> advise Richards to go to the Chatham Islands, because on my suggestion Judge Travers sent his son there (at an expense of nearly £300 - -) &amp; thus I published 2 years ago a full account of the vegetation,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.02.</p>
               </note> which beyond <name key="Myositidium%20nobile">Myositidium nobile</name> contains nothing very ornamental.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With kindest regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller M.D.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Could Richards not manage to go to New Guinea,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Guinea<seg style="font-style: italic; "> above</seg> Caledonia<seg style="font-style: italic; "> deleted.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> to the German missionary station? Pray give him my best regards. What will be the price of a full set of Richards' plants.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Myositidium%20nobile">Myositidium nobile</name>
            </p>
         </div>
